sentences.sContent: Insufficient resources have been devoted to the health service.
sentences.sCn: 用于医疗保健服务的资源不足。

sentences.sContent: ...The expert review also found insufficient evidence to recommend any drugs or dietary supplements that could prevent or slow cognitive decline...
...and many experts rightly worry about a "lost generation" of mostly Hispanic Texans with insufficient skills for the demands of the knowledge economy...
...to which Google has arguably paid insufficient attention...

words.tran: 不足，不充分；机能不全；不适当

trans.tranOther: not enough, or not great enough
